    "2026-07-01 V15m — Invoke-site cancellation checkpoint and completed-callee-finality witness (paired with V15m-T; cancellation.md §Granularity cka-47 V15m invoke facet, invocation.md, errors-and-results/error-model.md ERR-13): fills runInvokeChild(checkpoint, signal, site, child) in src/runtime/invoke-cancellation.ts — the two cancellation facets that ride on the live invoke execution surface, split out of V15a per conventions.md §smallest-shippable-leaf. It awaits checkpoint.before(\"invoke\", site) immediately before the child spawn (the invoke per-site presence arm distributed off V17c; V8a Checkpoint seam PIC-10), reads signal.aborted and returns { kind: \"cancelled\", committed: [] } on an observed abort (the child is never spawned), otherwise drives the child via child.drive() and surfaces { kind: \"value\", result, committed: child.committed }. Those committed side effects stay final under any downstream ? / panic / cancel (ERR-13, delegated live-carrier witness for V4f's completed-callee-finality deferral) because the runtime holds no compensating / rollback path (handleNoRollbackTerminalEvent, V4f) — finality is observed by construction. No new diagnostics-registry codes. Pure async function — no module-level mutable state / broad catch / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call. All 5 V15m-T tests green; typecheck + lint clean. The 4 pre-existing V4g-T reds in an unrelated subsystem (tests/pre-evaluation-reload-failure.test.ts, red on HEAD without this change) are unaffected.",
