    "2026-07-01 V14d — Code-tool host-denial surface (paired with V14d-T; pi-integration-contract/trust-boundary.md §\"No additional access channels\" PIC-52): fills isHostDenial and classifyHostDenial in src/runtime/tool-call-host-denial.ts. isHostDenial recognises a host-side denial — a value thrown from execute(), or a tool return with isError:true — and rejects a non-denial return (isError absent or falsy). classifyHostDenial routes both denial forms to Err(CodeToolError { kind:\"code_tool\", cause:\"execution\", tool_name }), never a silent Ok: the throw form reuses V14g's lowerToolExecuteThrow coercion/truncation, the isError:true form carries the joined denial text (filterJoinToolText) under the same CODE_TOOL_MESSAGE_MAX_BYTES code-point-boundary cap; only a non-denial return lowers to Ok(<joined text>), so the content-only accepted-path lowering can no longer silently succeed on an isError:true denial. Pure functions; no globals/statics/singletons, no broad catch, no ambient primitive, no Promise combinator, no Sync call. All 8 V14d-T tests green; typecheck + lint clean. The 4 pre-existing V4g-T reds in an unrelated subsystem (tests/pre-evaluation-reload-failure.test.ts, red on HEAD without this change) are unaffected.",
    "2026-07-01 V14d-T — Code-tool host-denial surface tests (paired V14d impl; pi-integration-contract/trust-boundary.md §\"No additional access channels\" PIC-52): adds src/runtime/tool-call-host-denial.ts — the host-denial classification seam building on the V14a CodeToolError carrier and V14g execute()-throw lowering. Declares HostDeniableEnvelope ({ content?, isError? }), the HostToolOutcome union (throw / return), the HostDenialLowering disposition (denied with the CodeToolError carrier / accepted), and stubs both behaviour-bearing functions inertly: isHostDenial → false, classifyHostDenial → the forbidden silent-Ok accepted outcome for every input. Plus tests/tool-calls-host-denial.test.ts with 8 tests, each citing PIC-52 inline: a thrown host-side denial → denied / Err(CodeToolError { kind:\"code_tool\", cause:\"execution\", tool_name }) / never a silent Ok; an { content, isError: true } host return → denied / Err(CodeToolError { cause:\"execution\" }) / never a silent Ok even with resolvable content text (the content-only lowering would otherwise silently succeed); isHostDenial recognises both denial forms and rejects non-denials; a non-denial return → Ok(<joined text>) (the guard does not over-fire). Divergence: per F-1578 the code-side AgentToolResult type carries no isError, so the isError:true code-side path PIC-52 enumerates is modelled as a defensive guard on an optional envelope flag rather than a declared field — see notes.md / decisions.jsonl. Inert stub seam: no module-level mutable state / broad catch / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call. Typecheck + lint clean; all 8 tests red on their own primary assertions because the V14d body is absent — fail-red-for-the-intended-reason. The 4 pre-existing V4g-T reds in an unrelated subsystem (tests/pre-evaluation-reload-failure.test.ts, red on HEAD without this change) are unaffected.",
    "2026-07-01 V14c — Code-side tool-call off-surface outcome routing (paired with V14c-T; tool-calls.md §\"Outcome enumeration\", cancellation.md §\"Race semantics\" CNCL-1/2/3, pi-integration-contract/host-interfaces-core.md §\"Tool execution from loom code\"): fills the four behaviour-bearing functions in src/runtime/tool-call-off-surface.ts so each off-surface code-tool outcome surfaces on its own channel rather than all on loom/runtime/internal-error. routeLoomCallableSetupThrow translates a captured .loom-callable parallel-batch adapter setup throw into a clean { isError: true, content:[text(\"loom <name> aborted with internal error: <error.message>\")] } value carrying the bare callable-set name (never /<name>) and in parallel emits exactly one loom/runtime/internal-error diagnostic (message \"internal error: <error.message>\", hint error.stack or \"<no stack available>\" when falsy) and one loom-system-note. routeToolReturnShape inspects the resolved envelope in the lowering procedure's inspection order (resolved-not-object → content-not-iterable → entry-missing-type → entry-missing-text; other for a throwing getter) and routes a non-conforming shape to internal-error with details.kind=\"tool-return-shape\"/details.tool_name/details.shape_check — off the CodeToolError surface — lowering a conforming envelope to Ok(<joined text>) via lowerResolvedToolEnvelope with no defect emission. awaitToolSettlementOrAbort races the execute() Promise against loomAbort.signal with no internal timeout (NOCEIL-1): a non-settling Promise blocks until the signal fires → CodeToolError { cause:\"cancelled\" } with no internal-error, keeping a swallowing rejection handler attached from construction so a late reject never reaches Node unhandledRejection. discardPostCancelSettlement is a total no-op — no rebind (CNCL-1), no second Err (CNCL-2), no second RuntimeEvent (CNCL-3), no diagnostic of any severity, discarded value not traversed. The return-shape inspection's broad catch at the Pi-owned resolved value carries // allow-broad-catch: pi-sdk-boundary; no globals/statics/singletons, no ambient primitive, no Promise combinator, no Sync call. All 15 V14c-T tests green; typecheck + lint clean. The 4 pre-existing V4g-T reds in an unrelated subsystem (tests/pre-evaluation-reload-failure.test.ts, red on HEAD without this change) are unaffected."
